topics.create_sql:
CREATE TABLE topics (
	id INTEGER NOT NULL, 
	title VARCHAR(200) NOT NULL, 
	category VARCHAR(100), 
	content TEXT, 
	created_at DATETIME, 
	updated_at DATETIME, 
	PRIMARY KEY (id)
)

assignments.create_sql:
CREATE TABLE assignments (
	id INTEGER NOT NULL, 
	type VARCHAR(9), 
	title VARCHAR(200), 
	description TEXT, 
	due_date DATETIME, 
	created_at DATETIME, 
	PRIMARY KEY (id)
)

topic_versions.create_sql:
CREATE TABLE topic_versions (
	id INTEGER NOT NULL, 
	topic_id INTEGER, 
	content TEXT, 
	version INTEGER, 
	changed_by VARCHAR(100), 
	change_reason TEXT, 
	created_at DATETIME, 
	PRIMARY KEY (id), 
	FOREIGN KEY(topic_id) REFERENCES topics (id)
)

keywords.create_sql:
CREATE TABLE keywords (
	id INTEGER NOT NULL, 
	topic_id INTEGER, 
	keyword VARCHAR(100), 
	PRIMARY KEY (id), 
	FOREIGN KEY(topic_id) REFERENCES topics (id)
)

mnemonics.create_sql:
CREATE TABLE mnemonics (
	id INTEGER NOT NULL, 
	topic_id INTEGER, 
	mnemonic VARCHAR(100), 
	full_text TEXT, 
	PRIMARY KEY (id), 
	FOREIGN KEY(topic_id) REFERENCES topics (id)
)

exam_history.create_sql:
CREATE TABLE exam_history (
	id INTEGER NOT NULL, 
	topic_id INTEGER, 
	exam_round VARCHAR(50), 
	question_number VARCHAR(50), 
	score FLOAT, 
	PRIMARY KEY (id), 
	FOREIGN KEY(topic_id) REFERENCES topics (id)
)

submissions.create_sql:
CREATE TABLE submissions (
	id INTEGER NOT NULL, 
	assignment_id INTEGER, 
	user_id VARCHAR(100), 
	file_path VARCHAR(500), 
	submitted_at DATETIME, 
	score FLOAT, 
	feedback TEXT, 
	PRIMARY KEY (id), 
	FOREIGN KEY(assignment_id) REFERENCES assignments (id)
)

categories.create_sql:
CREATE TABLE categories (
	id INTEGER NOT NULL, 
	name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL, 
	description TEXT, 
	parent_id INTEGER, 
	created_at DATETIME, 
	PRIMARY KEY (id), 
	FOREIGN KEY(parent_id) REFERENCES categories (id)
)

templates.create_sql:

	id INTEGER NOT NULL, 
	name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL, 
	description TEXT, 
	content TEXT NOT NULL, 
	category VARCHAR(100), 
	created_at DATETIME, 
	updated_at DATETIME, 
	PRIMARY KEY (id)
)

	id INTEGER NOT NULL,

exam_questions.create_sql:
CREATE TABLE exam_questions (
	id INTEGER NOT NULL, 
	weekly_exam_id INTEGER, 
	session INTEGER NOT NULL, 
	question_number INTEGER NOT NULL, 
	question_text TEXT NOT NULL, 
	question_type VARCHAR(12) NOT NULL, 
	created_at DATETIME, 
	PRIMARY KEY (id), 
	FOREIGN KEY(weekly_exam_id) REFERENCES weekly_exams (id)
)
